To determine why the BP flakes are coated on the GBs only, we measured the contact angle of IPA on perovskite films with different crystallinities (Fig. S9). The average contact angles are 8°, 16° and 27° for the amorphous, polycrystalline and single-crystal perovskite surfaces, respectively, indicating that the contact angle of IPA decreases with the decreasing crystallinity of perovskite films. The surface energy of IPA on a perovskite film is related to the contact angle θ provided by Young’s equation39:1cosθ=γSV−γSLγLV\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
